
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lzmore` baraye didan file-haye ziad bozorg ke ba `gzip` ya `lzma` feshorde shode-and, estefade mishavad.  Mesle `more` ast, ama baraye file-haye feshorde kar mikonad. Yani dige niaz nist aval az halat feshordegi dar biarid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lzmore +<number>` --> 🔢 Shoroo az khatte moshakhas shomare `<number>`  
    🔹 `lzmore -d`      --> 📂  Estefade az dastoor digar (`program`) baraye baz kardane file, agar `LZMORE` taeen shode bashad.
    🔹 `lzmore -f`      --> 📄 Namayesh file-ha be soorate majmooei (agar chand file dade shode bashad).
    🔹 `lzmore -p <command>` --> 🚦 Estefade az `command` baraye safhe safhe kardan (paging).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lzmore myfile.gz

    🔹 Didan file-e `myfile.gz` safhe be safhe.

    $ lzmore +20 myfile.lzma

    🔹 Didan file-e `myfile.lzma` az khatte 20 shoroo shode.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lzmore logfile.gz

    🔹 File `logfile.gz` ra safhe be safhe namayesh midahad, va shoma mitavanid ba zadan dokmeye `space` be safhe badi beravid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lzmore` command is used to view large compressed files (gzip or lzma) one page at a time.  It functions similarly to `more` but handles compressed files directly, eliminating the need to decompress them first.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lzmore +<number>` --> 🔢 Start displaying from the specified line number `<number>`.
    🔹 `lzmore -d`      --> 📂  Use the program specified by the `LZMORE` environment variable for viewing.
    🔹 `lzmore -f`      --> 📄 Treat files as a logical sequence (if multiple files are given).
    🔹 `lzmore -p <command>` --> 🚦 Use the specified `command` as the pager.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lzmore myfile.gz

    🔹 View the file `myfile.gz` one page at a time.

    $ lzmore +20 myfile.lzma

    🔹 View the file `myfile.lzma`, starting from line 20.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ lzmore logfile.gz

    🔹 Displays the `logfile.gz` page by page, allowing you to navigate using the `space` key.
